item.more-axolotl.axolotl_catalog.toolti: Not everything in here applies to the game in 100% correctness
more-axolotl.desc.minecraft.lucy:
Probably the most famous
axolotl type!

Leucistic or Lucy are the
most common Axolotl.
Normally Leucistic Axolotls
have a pink tone of color.

Obtained: Natural Spawning
more-axolotl.desc.minecraft.wild:
Most closely resembles the
specimens from Lake Xochimilco!

Wild have little details on skin.
Normally Wild Axolotls have
darker tones or brown color.

Obtained: Natural Spawning
more-axolotl.desc.minecraft.gold:
Characterized by its bright
Gold skin similar to the ore,
this morph is the result of
almost all pigments being
suppressed except for one
that causes Gold.
They look so valuable!

Obtained: Natural Spawning
more-axolotl.desc.minecraft.cyan:
No detailed description provided

Obtained: Natural Spawning
more-axolotl.desc.minecraft.blue:
Originates from a suggestion
from r/Minecraft to Mojang!
The Blue Axolotl is based on
the Mudkip Pokemon.
Blue Axolotls are the most rare
ones in Minecraft Vanilla,
although some people think
it exists in Realife, it doesn't!

Obtained: Rare Breeding
more-axolotl.desc.more-axolotl.albino:
No detailed description provided

Obtained: Natural Spawning
more-axolotl.desc.more-axolotl.black:
No detailed description provided

Obtained: Natural Spawning
more-axolotl.desc.more-axolotl.chimera:
Morph that looks like
a fused version!

Chimera have little details on
skin like wild.
Chimera morphs are created
when two eggs fuse together
in development, and each side
grows according to the egg
it came from.

Obtained: Breeding Lucy, Wild
more-axolotl.desc.more-axolotl.enigma:
One of the most
interesting morphs.

Enigma's details are parts
of the skin of Gold and Black,
a mix of beautiful colors
making an unique texture.

Obtained: Breeding Gold, Black
more-axolotl.desc.more-axolotl.firefly:
Morph that has two colors
inherited from its parents,
Black and Albino.

There are only less than a
dozen specimens of this type
in the world that were created
by Lloyd Strohl II.
The most beautiful part are
the split colors!

Obtained: Breeding Black, Albino
more-axolotl.desc.more-axolotl.firefly_i:
Morph that has two colors
inherited from its parents,
Black and Albino.

There are only less than a
dozen specimens of this type
in the world that were created
by Lloyd Strohl II.
The most beautiful part are
the split colors!

Obtained: Breeding Black, Albino
more-axolotl.desc.more-axolotl.lapis:
Doesn't really exist in real life.

Pictures of Black Axolotls on
some camera rolls, due to a color
reading error of the camera,
turn Blue.
Lapis is the blue with the
colors ported by Minecraft

Obtained: Natural Spawning
more-axolotl.desc.more-axolotl.neon:
The Neon/Green is a variant
that Mojang wanted to add
but never did!

The variant is probably
based on GFP Axolotls.
The first time it was shown was
in the Caves And Cliffs Trailer.

Obtained: Natural Spawning
more-axolotl.desc.more-axolotl.glow:
Based on Glow Squids.

This variant looks like
the Neon/Green.
Some say that an Axolotl
that lives in the deep sea can
evolve into glow axolotl!

Obtained: Natural Spawning
more-axolotl.desc.more-axolotl.piebald:
The most common of the
rare mutations.

The coloring is a Leucistic Axolotl
and Black has breed and mutated
to have pigment in places in other
than just their face

Obtained: Breeding Black, Albino
more-axolotl.desc.more-axolotl.gray:
No detailed description provided

Obtained: Natural Spawning
more-axolotl.desc.more-axolotl.shiny:
The shiny version of the
Blue Variant!
The Design is based on the
Shiny version of Mudkip Pokemon
that the Blue Variant represents.

Obtained: Rare Breeding
more-axolotl.desc.more-axolotl.mosaic_bl:
No detailed description provided

Obtained: Breeding Black, Lucy
more-axolotl.desc.more-axolotl.mosaic_wi:
No detailed description provided

Obtained: Breeding Wild, Lucy
more-axolotl.desc.more-axolotl.skeleton:
The little companion
of the undead.

The design was inspired
by the Skeleton.
It only consists of bones and
has no gills or skin.
Although it's probably already
dead it behaves like
any other axolotls.

Obtained: Rename to "skelotl"
more-axolotl.desc.more-axolotl.drowned:
The forgotten sea creature
of the depths of the sea.

The design of the
Drowned Axolotl was inspired
by the Drowned Zombie.
It has cyan eyes and has moss
all over it's body.

Obtained: Rename to "drownelotl"
more-axolotl.desc.more-axolotl.rainbow:
Probably the most
mind blowing axolotl!

These axolotls can change the
color of the pigments in an
extraordinary way.
These cases are resulting from
a rare genome of axolotls that
can occur in really rare cases.

Obtained: Rare Breeding
more-axolotl.desc.more-axolotl.sculk:
The Axolotl in process of the
evolution to survive in
the Deep Dark.

There are some Axolotls which
didnt evolved perfectly into
Wardens and got a look similar
to the Warden
while still being an axolotl.
This Axolotl is blind, cute...
but it can sense you!

Obtained: Natural Spawning
